---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 20, 2025',
  description: '10Web AI vs Durable AI: WordPress power with WooCommerce vs blazing-fast 30-second generation. 10Web wins for e-commerce (70% commission), Durable for speed. Tested and compared.',
  tool1: {
    name: '10Web AI',
    slug: '/reviews/10web'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Durable AI',
    slug: '/reviews/durable'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    tenweb: 'Best for WordPress sites and e-commerce',
    durable: 'Best for ultra-fast simple sites',
    winner: 'Speed: Durable. Features: 10Web. Pick your priority.'
};

---

<Layout title="10Web AI vs Durable AI: WordPress Features vs Blazing Speed" description={comparisonData.description}>

  <!-- WebPage Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: '10Web AI vs Durable AI: WordPress Features vs Blazing Speed',
      description: '10Web is WordPress with AI. Durable is the fastest AI builder (30 seconds). One gives you 60,000 plugins. The other generates complete sites before you can blink. Here\'s how to choose.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/10web-vs-durable'
    }}
  />

  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is better: 10Web or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Neither is objectively betterâ€”they solve different problems. 10Web (8.2/10) is WordPress with AI generationâ€”60,000 plugins, full WooCommerce e-commerce, code export, but requires WordPress knowledge and has slower PageSpeed (75-85). Durable (7.8/10) generates complete sites in 30 seconds with 95+ PageSpeed and zero technical knowledge required, but has no export, limited features, and no plugins. Choose Durable for speed and simplicity. Choose 10Web for e-commerce, content sites, and extensibility. If you need real e-commerce, 10Web is the only choice. If you need a simple site fast, Durable wins."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I switch from Durable to 10Web later?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Switching from Durable to 10Web is difficult and expensive. Durable doesn't export code at allâ€”zero code export. Your entire site (copy, images, layout, CRM data) is locked in Durable's platform. To move to 10Web/WordPress, you must rebuild from scratch. Real example: client spent $4,000 and 3 weeks rebuilding their site when they needed WordPress features Durable couldn't provide. If there's ANY chance you'll need e-commerce, memberships, content-heavy featuresâ€”start with 10Web. The rebuild cost is brutal. Durable is perfect only if you're 100% sure you'll never need WordPress features."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is 10Web good for beginners?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10Web is medium difficulty (7.0/10 ease). If you've never used WordPress, there's a learning curve. You'll learn WordPress themes, plugins, WooCommerce, updates, backups. It's more complex than Durable but far more powerful. For complete beginners, Durable (9.0/10 ease) is simpler. However, if you're willing to learn WordPress, 10Web gives you skills that transfer to 40% of all websites. WordPress knowledge is valuable long-term. Consider: Durable for zero learning curve, 10Web if you're willing to learn a valuable skill."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does 10Web have good e-commerce?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, 10Web has excellent e-commerce through WooCommerce integration. You get full WooCommerce features: product variants, inventory management, shipping zones, tax calculation, 60+ payment gateways, discount codes, product reviews, and more. WooCommerce powers 38% of all online stores for a reasonâ€”it's powerful and flexible. Durable has only basic e-commerce. If you're selling products beyond simple items, 10Web is the only viable choice. For serious online stores with inventory management, product variants, or scaling needs, 10Web with WooCommerce is professional-grade."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How fast is Durable's PageSpeed?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable delivers 95+ PageSpeed scores consistently. Sites load in under 1 second (0.9s in real testing). This is significantly faster than 10Web's 75-85 PageSpeed and 2+ second load times. Durable's speed advantage comes from: optimized proprietary platform, minimal bloat, no plugin overhead, and aggressive caching. For local businesses, simple portfolios, and lead generation sites where speed directly impacts conversions, Durable's performance is excellent. However, this speed comes at the cost of featuresâ€”you're trading flexibility for performance."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Durable have code export?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, Durable does NOT offer any code export. Your website is permanently locked into Durable's platform. You cannot download your site, move to another host, or hire a developer to modify the code. This is the most significant limitation of Durable. If client handoff, potential exit, or platform independence matters, Durable is the wrong choice. 10Web exports standard WordPressâ€”you can move to any host, hire any WordPress developer, or modify the code freely. Code export is critical for agencies, client work, or anyone who values ownership and portability."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does 10Web cost vs Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10Web pricing: $10-60/month depending on features and plan. Durable pricing: $15-20/month. At the low end, 10Web ($10/mo) is cheaper than Durable ($15/mo). At the high end, 10Web's premium plan ($60/mo) costs more but includes enterprise features. However, consider total cost of ownership: 10Web may require paid plugins for advanced features, while Durable includes everything. One client saved $1,200+ over 3 years using Durable instead of 10Web for a simple service business. Factor in your specific needsâ€”both tools offer competitive pricing for their target use cases."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

