            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Features vs Speed</span>
          </h1>

          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              10Web is WordPress with AI generationâ€”60,000 plugins, full e-commerce, but requires WordPress knowledge. Durable generates complete sites in 30 secondsâ€”simple, fast, but limited. One's a powerhouse, one's a sprinter.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
            Use Durable if you need a simple site fast (30 seconds fast).<br />
            Use 10Web if you need WordPress power, e-commerce, or extensibility.<br /><br />
            Durable wins on speed and ease. 10Web wins on features and flexibility.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
