          <li>PageSpeed matters more than features</li>
          <li>You're non-technical</li>
          <li>You want built-in CRM/lead capture</li>
          <li>You don't care about exporting</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web and Durable solve different problems. 10Web gives you WordPress powerâ€”extensible, portable, familiar, but complex and slower. Durable gives you speedâ€”30-second generation, 95+ PageSpeed, zero technical knowledge required, but limited.<br /><br />
          For local businesses, simple portfolios, lead gen sitesâ€”Durable is perfect. For e-commerce, content sites, anything complexâ€”10Web is the only viable choice.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
          <a href={comparisonData.tool1.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read 10Web review
          </a>
          <a href={comparisonData.tool2.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
